laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Human chorionic gonadotropin and alpha-fetoprotein levels
Levels of urea nitrogen, creatinine, glucose, conjugated and total bilirubin, albumin, electrolytes, aspartate aminotransferase, alanine aminotransferase, and lactate dehydrogenase

laboratory_examinations.date: Two years after treatment for seminoma

laboratory_examinations.findings: No evidence of deep venous thrombosis
No evidence of cancer; organizing fibrin, reactive bronchial epithelial cells, histiocytes, and lymphocytes present; no malignant cells found.
Pulmonary nodules and peripheral opacities had become less opaque; some slightly increased in size; multiple new peripheral densities present.
Waning and waxing peripheral nodular opacities; representative CT images showed some nodules smaller and new lesions appeared.
Regression of some nodules and enlargement of others; no new nodules identified.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Esophageal motility and 24-hour esophageal pH-probing studies
laboratory_examinations.findings: Consistent with the presence of severe gastroesophageal reflux disease.
